File: README.md
# test-website
A small, static web project used to demonstrate a simple HTML page that links to CSS and JavaScript. The page shows a welcome header and displays an alert saying "Hello, world!" when loaded.

How to view
- Open test-website/index.html in a web browser.
- You should see a welcome header. When the page loads, an alert with the message "Hello, world!" will appear.

Notes
- The CSS is linked in the head, and the JavaScript is loaded at the end of the body to ensure proper loading order.

If you’d like, I can tailor the structure or styling further (for example, add navigation, more content, or responsiveness).
