  - A Python backend exposing a /chat endpoint for the Unity client.
  - A README with setup steps and OBS guidance.

What to tell yourself as you proceed (practical tips)
- Start small and iterate: MVP first, then progressively add Vision, then Code Understanding, then Emotion/ Mouth complexity.
- Keep interfaces clean and swap-friendly: abstract the GPT model behind an IGptModel interface; you can switch to other models down the line without changing Unity code.
- Use existing assets judiciously: lip-sync assets, facial rigs, and standard Twitch libraries to reduce time-to-delivery.
- Documentation is as important as code: maintain a design document, update the README, and keep a CHANGELOG as you add features.
- Safety first: implement consent prompts for window capture and add moderation for chat and content.

Sample user-facing run instructions (concise)
- Prerequisites: Unity, Python, OBS, an AI model API key (or local model), Twitch account and stream key.
