10) OBS and streaming integration
- Subgoals:
  - Create an OBS WebSocket bridge to control an in-scene timer overlay (increase time on new followers/subs).
  - Build a simple overlay protocol: the Unity app can send events to OBS to update overlay text or timer.
  - Ensure the Unity window can be captured by OBS or use a virtual webcam/NDI pipeline if needed.
- Why this matters: The prompt requested dynamic OBS timer logic and seamless streaming integration.

11) Debug UI, monitoring, and diagnostics
- Subgoals:
  - Implement in-scene and in-editor debug panels showing AI state, emotion state, last messages, queue lengths, latency, and input sources.
  - Build a lightweight inspector-like window to monitor chat, memory, and perception data.
