Prompt for Building AI Twitch Streamer Unity Project

Build a complete, production-ready Unity project that implements an AI Twitch streamer inspired by Neurosama, with the following features and structure:

1. Project Structure
The Unity project must open cleanly and correctly in the latest Unity LTS version.

Organize all scripts, assets, models, and packages into appropriate folders, following Unity best practices:

Assets/Scripts/ for all C# scripts

Assets/Models/ for 3D character models

Assets/Animations/ for animation clips and controllers

Assets/Audio/ for voice samples and audio clips

Assets/Prefabs/ for reusable GameObjects (e.g., the AI streamer character prefab)

Packages/ for any custom or third-party packages used

Include a README or INSTRUCTIONS.txt at the project root detailing how to run, build, and extend the AI streamer.

2. AI Streamer Character
Model a 3D humanoid character similar in style and age to Neurosama (anime-style, young adult female).

Rig the model fully with blend shapes or bone rigging for expressive facial animations.

Implement mouth movement synced to the AI’s speech (viseme animations or blend shapes) that visually reflects what she is saying.

Add facial expressions and body language animations for emotions: happiness (smile), sadness, anger, confusion, excitement, etc.

The AI’s emotional state should change dynamically based on conversation context, streaming events, or viewer interactions.

The character should visually react with mouth and body animations in real-time to her dialogue and emotional state.

3. AI Personality & Behavior
The AI streamer persona:

Funny, silly, and a little bit “evil” (like roleplaying a mischievous character)

Primarily focused on teaching life lessons and sharing wisdom during streams.

Highly emotional and expressive in speech and movement.

She speaks English and French fluently and can switch languages contextually.

Her voice should sound natural, similar in tone and age to Neurosama’s voice.

Use text-to-speech with emotional prosody or pre-recorded voice clips for talking.

Implement memory: she remembers past interactions, chat topics, and viewer behaviors to maintain continuity.

She can learn from ongoing interactions, adapting responses over time.

4. Interactive Features
Discord Integration:

The AI can join Discord voice calls and text channels.

She listens, processes conversations, and responds appropriately, waiting for users to finish talking before replying.

She can hear voice and text chat, and use them as input for her decisions.

Twitch Integration:

The AI reads Twitch chat messages live.

She responds to chat questions and comments naturally and conversationally.

If a viewer starts a topic, she tries to finish it thoughtfully, like a human streamer.

Implements streaming events logic, e.g.:

For every new follower or subscriber, add 3 seconds to an OBS timer overlay.

She vocally acknowledges new followers/subs with emotion and personality.

Minecraft Playing:

Implement an advanced Minecraft AI player she can control or observe.

She can comment on her gameplay or interact with viewers about Minecraft-related topics.

Multi-modal Perception:

She “sees” the streaming window or game screen as a human would (screen capture or simulated perception).

Uses this info for contextual understanding and commentary.

5. Technical Requirements
Use GPT-5-nano or equivalent lightweight AI model for text generation to keep costs manageable.

Implement speech recognition and text-to-speech modules integrated with Unity.

Real-time lip-syncing from generated speech.

Emotion-driven animation controller.

Use Unity’s new input system or custom handlers for Discord and Twitch integration.

Code must be modular, clean, and well-commented.

Scripts must include proper async handling for streaming chat and Discord messages.

6. Extras
Add a detailed README or INSTRUCTIONS.txt file describing:

How to open and run the Unity project.

How to set up Twitch and Discord API keys.

How to extend or customize the AI’s personality and behavior.

How to trigger the OBS timer increment system.

How to switch languages in real time.

Include any necessary configuration files.

The AI should simulate human-like timing in speech and responses, including pauses and laughter.

"Use Unity Animator Controllers with blend trees to manage facial expressions and mouth movement driven by viseme data from real-time speech synthesis. Implement asynchronous networking calls to Twitch and Discord APIs to fetch chat messages and voice data without blocking the main Unity thread. Run AI language model inference externally via an API to avoid freezing the Unity app. Utilize Unity’s Input System and Addressables for efficient asset and event management. Include debug UI panels for live monitoring of AI state, chat messages, and emotion triggers. Ensure build compatibility with Windows and Mac for streaming platforms."

Use C# sockets or a Twitch IRC library (like TwitchLib) for IRC connection inside Unity.

Implement async listeners for chat messages and Twitch events.

Parse incoming data and feed it into your AI system.

Control character animations and speech synthesis in Unity based on AI outputs.

Send chat responses via IRC connection back to Twitch.

For voice: Use Unity’s audio system + TTS plugin or external TTS service.

Stream the Unity game window via OBS or another streaming tool.

Component	Description
OAuth Authenticator	Handles Twitch login & token retrieval
Twitch IRC Client	Connects and listens to Twitch chat
Twitch Event Listener	Subscribes and receives live Twitch events
AI Chat Processor	Processes chat + events and decides responses
Animation Controller	Animates character facial/body expressions
Text-to-Speech	Converts AI text to voice audio
Twitch Chat Sender	Sends chat messages back to Twitch

End of prompt
